---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/widgets/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/widgets/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Legal - Axiora">
  <Header />
  
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Axiora Legal Documents</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
          Last Updated: March 28, 2026
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Welcome to Axiora's legal documentation. This page contains our Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, and Refund Policy. 
          These documents outline your rights and responsibilities when using Axiora, how we handle your data, and our refund procedures. 
          Please read these documents carefully. By using Axiora, you agree to these terms and policies.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="#terms" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors">
            Terms of Service
          </a>
          <a href="#privacy" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors">
            Privacy Policy
          </a>
          <a href="#refund" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors">
            Refund Policy
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Terms of Service -->
      <div id="terms" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8 scroll-mt-20">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">1. Terms of Service</h1>
        
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 28, 2026</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.1 Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          By creating an account on Axiora, you ("User," "you," or "your") agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, you may not create an account or use the Axiora platform. Your continued use of Axiora after any modifications to these Terms constitutes acceptance of the updated version.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.2 Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Axiora is a desktop application designed for single-file data analysis, supporting CSV and Excel formats. The Service allows you to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Upload a data file and receive an AI-generated summary, including business domain identification, process detection, and data insights</li>
          <li>Generate analysis questions that are automatically converted into interactive charts within a customizable dashboard</li>
          <li>Receive AI-generated business recommendations</li>
          <li>Interact with your data through a conversational chat interface</li>
          <li>Share reports with other users via the <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-700 px-1 rounded">.axr</code> file format</li>
          <li>Export reports as PDF or PowerPoint files</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Axiora consists of two parts: the <strong>Website</strong> (axiora.software), where you can learn about the product, download the application, manage your subscription, and track usage; and the <strong>Desktop Application</strong>, where all data analysis takes place.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>AI Processing:</strong> Axiora uses external Large Language Model (LLM) APIs to power its analysis features. When you use AI-powered features, your prompts are sent to Axiora's servers and forwarded to the LLM provider. No raw dataset, dataset metadata, AI prompts, or AI responses are stored on Axiora's remote servers. All such data remains on your local device. Only your account information and usage metadata are stored remotely.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.3 User Eligibility</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Axiora is available to any individual or entity capable of entering into a binding legal agreement under applicable law. By creating an account, you represent that you have the legal capacity to accept these Terms.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.4 User Responsibilities and Prohibited Conduct</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You are solely responsible for how you use Axiora and the data you upload. By using the Service, you agree <strong>not</strong> to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Upload, process, or analyze any data that is illegal, stolen, obtained without authorization, or that violates any applicable law or regulation</li>
          <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose, including but not limited to fraud, money laundering, or any activity that violates local, national, or international law</li>
          <li>Attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to derive the source code, algorithms, or underlying technology of the Axiora application or its servers</li>
          <li>Spam, abuse, or attempt to overload Axiora's servers or API endpoints through excessive, automated, or unauthorized requests</li>
          <li>Share, sell, transfer, or allow unauthorized access to your Axiora account credentials</li>
          <li>Attempt to circumvent any usage limits, subscription restrictions, or security measures</li>
          <li>Use the Service to harm, harass, or infringe upon the rights of any third party</li>
          <li>Introduce malware, viruses, or any malicious code through the Service</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Axiora reserves the right to suspend or terminate your account immediately if you violate any of the above.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.5 Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Axiora's IP:</strong> The Axiora software, application, website, branding, trademarks, and underlying technology are the exclusive intellectual property of Axiora. Nothing in these Terms grants you any rights to Axiora's software, code, or brand.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Your IP:</strong> All data files you upload, as well as all reports, charts, insights, dashboards, and analysis outputs generated from your data, are and remain your exclusive property. Axiora does not claim any ownership over your data or the outputs you generate using the Service. You are solely responsible for ensuring you have the right to upload and process any data you submit.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.6 Account Termination</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Termination by You:</strong> You may delete your account at any time through the account settings on the Axiora website.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Termination by Axiora:</strong> Axiora reserves the right to suspend or terminate your account without prior notice if you violate these Terms, engage in fraudulent activity, or abuse the Service.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Post-Termination Conditions:</strong> Upon account deletion or termination:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>If you have never subscribed to a paid plan (free trial users only), your account will be permanently closed immediately</li>
          <li>If you have previously subscribed to at least one paid plan and do not have an active running plan with remaining tokens, your account will be closed but restorable within <strong>3 months</strong> of the termination date</li>
          <li>You may not create a new Axiora account using the same email address associated with a terminated account</li>
          <li>Any active subscription with unused tokens at the time of termination will be forfeited without refund, unless otherwise required by applicable law</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.7 Disclaimers and Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 uppercase">
          The service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Axiora shall not be liable for:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Any data, reports, or analysis outputs you choose to share with third parties through or outside of the Axiora application</li>
          <li>Any unauthorized access to your device, local storage, or files resulting from third-party actions, including hacking, malware, or security breaches on your own hardware or network</li>
          <li>Any actions taken by the LLM provider with respect to data transmitted during AI processing, including but not limited to any use of transmitted data for model training or any other purpose governed by the LLM provider's own policies</li>
          <li>Any indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of or inability to use the Service</li>
          <li>Loss of data or business interruption</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          You acknowledge that AI-generated outputs, including summaries, insights, recommendations, and chart data, are generated automatically and may not always be accurate. You are solely responsible for validating any analysis before making business decisions based on it.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.8 Payments and Billing</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          All payments for Axiora subscriptions are processed by <strong>Paddle</strong> (paddle.com), our authorized Merchant of Record. This means that when you purchase a subscription:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li>You are transacting directly with Paddle, not with Axiora</li>
          <li>Paddle is the legal seller of record and is responsible for processing your payment, issuing invoices, and handling applicable taxes</li>
          <li>Your payment information (credit card details, billing address, etc.) is collected and managed exclusively by Paddle and is never seen or stored by Axiora</li>
          <li>Paddle's own Terms of Service and Privacy Policy apply to all payment transactions. We encourage you to review them at paddle.com</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Subscription access, token quotas, and plan features are managed by Axiora and governed by these Terms.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.9 Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United States. Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of the Service shall first be attempted to be resolved through good-faith negotiation. If a resolution cannot be reached, disputes shall be submitted to binding arbitration in accordance with applicable United States arbitration rules.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 italic text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
          <strong>Note:</strong> Disputes related to payment transactions are subject to Paddle's own dispute resolution process, as Paddle is the Merchant of Record for all purchases.
        </blockquote>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.10 Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Axiora reserves the right to modify these Terms at any time. If material changes are made, you will be notified via email sent to the address associated with your account at least <strong>14 days</strong> before the changes take effect. Your continued use of the Service after the effective date constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">1.11 Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-2">
          For questions about these Terms, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> contact@axiora.software</li>
          <li><strong>Support:</strong> support@axiora.software</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Privacy Policy -->
      <div id="privacy" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8 scroll-mt-20">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">2. Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 28, 2026</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Axiora ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your personal data.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.1 What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We collect the following categories of information:
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-2">
          <strong>Account Information:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-1">
          <li>Full name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-2">
          <strong>Usage Metadata:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-1">
          <li>Number of reports created</li>
          <li>Number of rows in datasets analyzed (not the dataset itself)</li>
          <li>Which AI features were used (summary, recommendations, dashboard, chat)</li>
          <li>Number of charts generated per report</li>
          <li>Number of chat messages exchanged per session</li>
          <li>AI model used per request</li>
          <li>Token consumption per request (input tokens, output tokens, total)</li>
          <li>Subscription plan and remaining token quota</li>
          <li>Timestamps of activity</li>
        </ul>
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 italic text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
          <strong>Important:</strong> We do not collect, store, or transmit your dataset contents, dataset metadata, AI prompts, or AI-generated analysis outputs to our remote servers. All of this data stays on your local device.
        </blockquote>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.2 How Data Is Collected</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We collect your data through the following means:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Account registration forms</strong> on the Axiora website when you sign up</li>
          <li><strong>Automatic usage tracking</strong> within the desktop application, which records activity metadata (as described above) and sends it to our servers in real time during your sessions</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.3 Why We Collect Your Data</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We use your data for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Service delivery:</strong> To authenticate your account, manage your subscription, enforce token quotas, and provide access to the Axiora application</li>
          <li><strong>Usage analytics:</strong> To understand how the product is used, improve features, and monitor system performance</li>
          <li><strong>Cost tracking:</strong> To accurately track AI token consumption and manage subscription billing</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To send you important account notifications, subscription updates, and updates to these policies</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.4 Who We Share Your Data With</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We do not currently sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for advertising or commercial purposes.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Paddle (Payment Processor & Merchant of Record):</strong> All subscription payments are processed by Paddle. When you make a purchase, Paddle collects and processes your payment information (card details, billing address, etc.) directly. Axiora does not receive or store your payment data. Paddle's collection and use of your payment information is governed by Paddle's own Privacy Policy, available at paddle.com.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          In the future, we may share limited data with:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Business partners</strong> who help us deliver or improve the Service</li>
          <li><strong>Advertisers</strong>, in aggregated and anonymized form only</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We may also disclose your data if required to do so by law, court order, or governmental authority.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We will update this Privacy Policy and notify you by email before any such sharing arrangements begin.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.5 Data Retention</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Account information and usage metadata</strong> are retained indefinitely while your account is active and after account deletion, subject to the conditions below</li>
          <li>Upon account deletion, your account details are retained for <strong>3 months</strong> to allow for account restoration</li>
          <li>Your <strong>email address</strong> is retained permanently after account deletion solely to prevent re-registration with the same email</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.6 Your Rights and Controls</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You have the following rights regarding your data:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Access your reports:</strong> From within the desktop application, you can view and manage all locally stored reports and analysis data</li>
          <li><strong>Delete local data:</strong> You may delete any reports or uploaded data directly from your device at any time</li>
          <li><strong>Delete your account:</strong> You may request account deletion through your account settings on the Axiora website. Upon deletion, your account information will be scheduled for removal after a 3-month retention window</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> Usage metadata associated with your account is retained even after account deletion for internal analytics purposes, in a form that does not identify you beyond a user record</li>
          <li><strong>Data requests:</strong> For any questions or requests regarding your personal data, contact us at contact@axiora.software or support@axiora.software</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.7 Cookies</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Axiora does not use cookies. No tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or analytics cookies are placed on your device through the Axiora website or desktop application.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.8 Third-Party LLM Processing</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          When you use AI-powered features in Axiora, your prompts are transmitted from your device to Axiora's servers and then forwarded to a third-party LLM provider for processing. The LLM provider's response is then returned to your device. Axiora does not store these prompts or responses on its remote servers. However, the LLM provider's own privacy policy and data practices apply to any data transmitted to their systems. We encourage you to review the applicable LLM provider's privacy policy.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.9 Contact for Privacy Matters</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-2">
          For any privacy-related questions, data access requests, or concerns:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> contact@axiora.software</li>
          <li><strong>Support:</strong> support@axiora.software</li>
          <li>Additional contact information and social media links are available on the Axiora website</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">2.10 Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Material changes will be communicated to you via email at least <strong>14 days</strong> before taking effect.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Refund Policy -->
      <div id="refund" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8 scroll-mt-20">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">3. Refund Policy</h1>
        
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 28, 2026</p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Axiora wants you to be satisfied with your subscription. This Refund Policy explains when and how refunds are issued. All payments are processed by <strong>Paddle</strong> as our Merchant of Record, and approved refunds are executed through Paddle back to your original payment method.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">3.1 Eligibility for a Refund</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You may be eligible for a refund if <strong>all</strong> of the following conditions are met:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>You have contacted Axiora support at support@axiora.software to initiate the refund process</li>
          <li>Your refund request is submitted within <strong>5 calendar days</strong> of your purchase date</li>
          <li>You have consumed <strong>less than 10%</strong> of your plan's token quota at the time of the request</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          If more than 10% of your token quota has been consumed, your purchase is non-refundable regardless of the time elapsed since purchase.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">3.2 How to Request a Refund</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          To request a refund:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Contact us at <strong>support@axiora.software</strong> with your account email and reason for the refund</li>
